This article is a transcript of remarks made by Vice President Mike Pence and President Donald Trump regarding the repeal and replacement of Obamacare. Pence introduces Trump as the President who will lead the effort to end Obamacare, and Trump thanks the group of Republican Congress members for their support in this endeavor. Trump criticizes the current state of Obamacare, promising that premiums and deductibles will come down with the new plan. He also expresses confidence that the plan will pass through the Senate and emphasizes the unity and hard work of the Republican Party. Trump introduces House Speaker Paul Ryan and praises him for his efforts in bringing the party together. He mentions that the plan will be followed by tax reform. Trump concludes by stating that he is confident in the success of his presidency and the plans for the future.